The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Atlas Copco India Ltd will issue bonus shares in the ratio of 1:1. The shareholders, at the recently held EGM, approved the issue, under which one equity share of Rs 10 will be issued for every share held, Atlas Copco informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The shares of the company were trading at Rs 1,180, down 1.09 per cent, on the BSE. Atlas Copco manufactures and sales air and gas compressors, construction and mining equipment and industrial tools. 

 Rohit Ferro Tech?s net profit increased to Rs 26.24 crore in the year ended March 31, from Rs 7.74 crore in the previous year. Net sales stood at Rs 127.4 crore, compared with previous year?s Rs 95.3 crore, a growth of 34 per cent. The board has recommended a maiden dividend of 10 per cent on the post-issue capital, which consists of 344,62,945 equity shares. 

 Gulshan Sugars amp; Chemicals has filed the draft prospectus with Sebi to enter the capital market with a fixed-price follow-on issue of 66,00,000 equity shares of Rs 8 each for a premium. The issue will constitute 51.51 per cent of the fully diluted post issue paid-up capital of the company. 

 Eveready Industries will invest Rs 60 crore to set up a plant in Uttaranchal to take its overall annual battery production capacity to 2 billion units.

 Strides Arcolab will form a 50:50 joint venture, Abdi Strides, with Turkey?s Abdi Ibrahim to introduce a range of specialty pharmaceutical products in Turkey and the neighbouring markets.

